entries.busy: I can't talk now, I'm working.
entries.bar28: That's it!  See you back at the palace!
entries.bar27: This one's done.  There's more Imperials on the way, cover me while I get the second truck running
entries.bar26: Good, you've got parts.  Keep me covered while I get this transport running
entries.bar25: You don't seem to have the parts yet.
entries.bar23: We're not out of the woods yet.  I'll get the truck, you get the parts.
entries.bar22: You don't know Jabba very well, do you?  Do you think he cares whose responsibility it was?  We'll all get thrown to the Rancor!
entries.bar21: What are you going to do?
entries.bar19: Oh.  A coward.  Well, you can either go get my parts or I can tell Jabba why he didn't get his shipment.
entries.bar18: I'm marking their location on your datapad.  Just get my parts back, I don't care how you do it.
entries.bar17: I'm not here to hunt down Jawas!
entries.bar15: Good, you've arrived.  Unfortunately, someone's stolen some of our engine parts.  It looks like Jawa tracks. Miserable little buggers.
entries.bar13: I don't have any more work for you right now.
entries.bar12: Bib Fortuna would like to speak with you again.
entries.bar11: Max Rebo, the bandleader, is in need of some assistance I hear.
entries.bar10: Go see Ephant Mon.  He has something he needs done.
entries.bar8: Jabba says to tell you thanks.  You've done a good job.
entries.bar7: Ok.  Come back and see me when you have time.
entries.bar6: Good.  I'm going to input the code to a self destruct device attached to one of Valarian's warehouses.  I just want you to go enter it and blow it up.  Simple enough?  Make sure you leave before that timer goes off!
entries.bar5: At the moment I'm a little busy.
entries.bar3: I'm Barada.  Bib says we can trust you, so I have some work for you to do.  Are you ready to do some work?
entries.bar2: I have work to do.  Come back when you've helped Yena.
entries.bar1: You shouldn't be here.  Go see Bib Fortuna if you need work.
